# Python Environment Policy (uv)

- Always use `uv run` for Python work in this project.
- Do not use the system Python interpreter directly.
- Do not invoke global `pytest` or other tools.
- Install dependencies with `uv sync` (with appropriate `--extra` flags).

## Examples

```bash
uv run pytest
```

```bash
uv run python script.py
```

```bash
uv sync --extra dev --extra dashboard
```
